Welcome to HERO Kids Sports.
Our promise: Fitness, Nutrition, Friends & Fun!

We have devised a specialized program that coaches kids in the fundamentals of their chosen sport, one step at a time.

Every program is specifically designed to teach your child the fundamentals of the sport and to learn how to be part of a team. We emphasize that no HERO works alone and can only succeed through helping others. 

Our programs start out with warm up sessions designed to teach children how to properly  prepare for exercise. Each week marks the completion of a new milestone in the basics of the sport. Join our HERO Kids Sports team today!

• Hero Kids Sports believes every child can succeed in life by developing confidence, motivation and a sense of belonging.
• All kids are capable and have the ability to be good at sports; they just need a little encouragement to learn.
• Younger, brighter minds! Our unique focus is 2-10 years of age. We know from years of experience of working with kids that the earlier kids start in sports, the more fun they have and the more they want to learn!

What HERO Does:
• We come to your school, park, house or residence to teach kids the fundamentals of sports.
• Through a unique child-focused introduction to team sports, we provide exceptional education in an inspiring atmosphere.
• HERO Kids Sports equips kids with the basics of a variety of athletics so that everyone can play as a team.
• Our program connects the essential components of a healthy life: being fit, eating healthy, having friends and feeling successful.

 

We are currently operating in the greater Boston area. Contact us directly by phone or email to find out if HERO is at your kid’s school!

SIGN UP NOW ... A Fun & Exciting Adventure/Obstacle Race for Adult & Kids ~ Donate Old Sneakers for Pediatric Cancer!
Official website: www.GreatAmazingRace.com

  Modeled after the TV show, THE GREAT AMAZiNG RACE (GAR) features teams of two racing against other teams around a cross country course speckled with fun-filled challenges. Teams that complete the challenges and arrive at finish line with fastest times are declared the winners. How well teammates work together (collaborate & communicate) is the most essential skill to winning the race.  1st place medals awarded to each division winner. 

   The race is open to everyone ... runners, joggers & walkers - pee wees to grandparents.  Be prepared to get a little dirty & wet. This race is way more fun than a 5k race!

RACE INFO
1. 1.5 mile cross country course with up to 8 challenges.
2. 2 person teams - adult/adult, adult/kid or kid/kid ... kids grades K-12..
3. 3 challenge levels ... easy, intermediate & difficult .. based on age & fitness level of racers. 
4. 4 race divisions ... based on grade of youngest member ... Grades K-2 / 3-5 / 6-8 / 9-Adult. 
5. Spectators can attend for FREE. 
6. Plan on 60 minutes to complete course ... Race happens rain or shine. 
7. Top 25 teams qualify for Championship Race and chance to win $1,000.

ADDITIONAL INFO
1. Special discounts for Teachers, Military & First Responders (police, fire, EMT) ... only available through the www.GreatAmazingRace.com registration portal only. 
2. Fund Raising. Local schools & youth organizations (scouts, youth teams, running clubs, churches, etc) can receive $ donations by participating in the race. Visit www.greatamazingrace.com for details. 
3. Sponsorship. Sponsorship with THE GREAT AMAZING RACE Series offers many exciting exposure possibilities for your company. Please contact us at info@greatamazingrace.com to discuss corporate and small business sponsorship opportunities.
4. Charity Partner. Help us fight pediatric cancer by donating 2 pairs of used sneakers or running shoes to Max Cure Foundation's Dunk Your Kicks program and receive a 2 minute time eraser token for the race. (www.DunkYourKicks.org)

Socks should not be worn because of the lack of traction on the equipment. Classes run from September through May and culminate in year-end performance with medals presented to every child in the Olympic Tradition. Instructor is Lorrie Rousseau. Greater Boston Area! 

 

Welcome to HERO Kids Sports.
Our promise: Fitness, Nutrition, Friends & Fun!

We have devised a specialized program that coaches kids in the fundamentals of their chosen sport, one step at a time.

Every program is specifically designed to teach your child the fundamentals of the sport and to learn how to be part of a team. We emphasize that no HERO works alone and can only succeed through helping others. 

Our programs start out with warm up sessions designed to teach children how to properly  prepare for exercise. Each week marks the completion of a new milestone in the basics of the sport. Join our HERO Kids Sports team today! 

HERO Kids Sports currently hosts 8 different sports for a period of six weeks at a time. We come to you and your kid at the school that they attend! 

If you do not see a sport that you would love to get your kid involved in, just let us know and we will work out the rest! Below is a brief description of each of the sports. For a more detailed breakdown of what each week entails, please contact us directly!

What HERO Believes:
• Hero Kids Sports believes every child can succeed in life by developing confidence, motivation and a sense of belonging.
• All kids are capable and have the ability to be good at sports; they just need a little encouragement to learn.
• Younger, brighter minds! Our unique focus is 2-10 years of age. We know from years of experience of working with kids that the earlier kids start in sports, the more fun they have and the more they want to learn!

What HERO Does:
• We come to your school, park, house or residence to teach kids the fundamentals of sports.
• Through a unique child-focused introduction to team sports, we provide exceptional education in an inspiring atmosphere.
• HERO Kids Sports equips kids with the basics of a variety of athletics so that everyone can play as a team.
• Our program connects the essential components of a healthy life: being fit, eating healthy, having friends and feeling successful.

 

We are currently operating in the greater Boston area. Contact us directly by phone or email to find out if HERO is at your kid’s school!

Since 2011, RED DRESS RUN has been a spectacle of fun and charitable giving. It is an approximately 5K "Hash Run," organized by the Northboro Hash House Harriers Running Club, an affiliate of the international Hash House Harriers. The 2016 event is in Worcester, MA, and all net proceeds will be donated to local charities.

 

On a Hash Run, some lead runners, called "Hares," take a head start to mark a spontaneous course with flour and chalk. When the Hash Run starts, the other runners, known as "Hounds," will chase after the flour and chalk marks to try and snare the Hares.

 

RED DRESS RUN honors a Hasher in Long Beach, CA who attended her first Hash, in 1987 while wearing a Red Dress instead of running clothes.  After being mocked for wearing that, she ran the course anyway, and other hashers of both sexes were so impressed that they began wearing a red dress as a joke. Soon, red dress runs became a tradition for Hashers around the world.

 

MEN AND WOMEN MUST  BE 21+ AND WEAR A RED DRESS TO PARTICIPATE!

Registration includes a hysterical 5K run, a fabulous t-shirt , a souvenir whistle, 4 drink tickets, dinner, and more!

 

The course for RED DRESS RUN is a closely guarded secret, but the Hares promise there will be three checkpoints to stop, take a drink, and socialize. Stopping at checkpoints is mandatory because the Hares will be there waiting for the last runner or walker to arrive before departing to continue marking the course. The course is not timed.

 

 

Event details and schedule

The 5K course is a secret,but it begins and ends at Three G's Sports Bar, 152 Milbury Street, Worcester, MA. Expect there to be some on-road and some off-road running. Show off your red dress and enjoy a cash bar starting at 12:00pm. The opening ceremonies start at 2:00pm, and you should expect to be on the course from approximately 2:00pm - 5:00pm. Don't miss the "Circle" ceremony after the run, at approximately 5:30pm - 6:00pm.

 

You must be 21+ years old, have proof of age, and be wearing a red dress to participate. Wear running shoes and be prepared to run or walk both on-road and off road on trails. The course is not timed, and everyone will wait for the last runner or walker at each checkpoint until the hares depart to continue marking the course.

 

RED DRESS RUN is hosted by the Northboro Hash House Harriers, a chapter of the International Hash House Harriers Runnng Club. 100% of net proceeds from the Red Dress Run will be donated to local charities.

 

For more information about the Northboro Hash House Harriers and about hashing, visit NorthboroH3.com.

America's Beer Run. 

At the BeerFit Running Series, we believe a good workout is made great with ice cold beer. Our community of runners value living in the moment, making memories with friends and leaving it all out on the racecourse. Whether it’s a casual jog or a road race, BeerFitters make the most of every mile and toast the journey every step of the way. Are you BeerFit?

Event details and schedule

The BeerFit Running Series featuring the Power Hour Run and Brew Mile to Boston on September 24, 2016! The race and free beer after-party will be held at Marshfield Fair, Boston and it’s going to be the best BeerFit yet, all in support of Water.org!

Event Schedule

  • Power Hour Run Check in opens at 7:00am
  • Power Hour race starts at 8:00am
  • Brew Mile Check in opens at 10:00am
  • Brew Mile race starts at 11:00am
  • Bars close at 1:00pm
  • Please pay close attention to your email for exact times & information leading up to the race.

 

Our Charity Partner

BeerFit Running Series benefits Water.org, a terrific organization co-founded by Gary White and Matt Damon, that has transformed hundreds of communities in Africa, South Asia, and Central America by providing access to safe water and sanitation.

 

The Benefits of Teaming Up

BeerFit Running Series is a challenging event, and it’s also a great party. Wouldn’t you agree that events and parties are best with friends? Grab yours, register, work on a team costume (or uniform), and make this experience one worth sharing on Instagram with your whole crew!

 

What You Need to Bring

  • ●     Your ID
  • ●     A print out of your registration confirmation email
  • ●     Some cash to get some food
  • ●     A solid plan of how you’re getting home safely after the event
  • ●     A big smile on that beautiful face of yours

 

Check-In

Bring your ID and your confirmation email/ticket fromActive.com that includes a barcode. No one will be admitted to the event unless you have a valid ID and are 21 years of age or older..

What’s Up with Spectators?

Spectators are more than welcome, assuming all spectators are 21 years of age or older.

 

Volunteering

BeerFit is a unique event that features the best of what each city has to offer. That includes the wonderful volunteers that make this event possible. We appreciate you, and that’s why volunteers receive a special edition BeerFit t-shirt, 2 free beers after their duties are completed, and the warm and fuzzy feeling that comes with being an awesome person. To join our list of volunteers in your city, please fill out this form!

Responsibility

The safety and well being of our participants and the local community are priority #1 for BeerFit. Follow these rules so we can all have a safe & epic time:

  • Every participant, spectator and designated driver who enter the event must be 21 years or older. No exceptions. To enter any BeerFit event you must have a valid ID. No ID = No entry.
  • Every participant and spectator must arrange for safe transportation post-event.
  • Brew Mile Specific
    • o   There is no requirement, rules or pressure to drink any of the beers on course during The Brew Mile
    • o   Each participant in the Brew Mile chooses, at their own discretion, whether they want to stop at a beer station on not
    • o   The beers provided during the Brew Mile are completely voluntary and each participant is limited to one (1) beer at each station. Water will be available at each beer station
  • We encourage everyone to celebrate running and beer responsibly with us

 

Other Questions?

 

Check the BeerFit FAQs!

Kylee's Kare Kits for Kidz is an organization that helps feed unfortuante children in Leominster, Ma. We currently feed 250 children in our town. It takes over $900 a week to feed our children. The food is distrubted in their back packs at their schools. The teacher's put them in the backpacks for them. We continue throughout the summer time to feed all of the children.

This is our second annual road race for our organization. All the monies go to feeding children, ages 3-18. Kylee is 13-years old. When she was 10 years old she noticed the children in the cafeteria eating breakfast. She went home and asked her grandmother, Lori why they ate there. Lori explained to her how some children do not have enough money to eat at home and some of them also get free lunches. She was worried about the children when they got home from school. She went to her principal with this concern and wanted to help. With the support of the principal, teachers, family, and her friends she started this organization. We started with 10 children and now we have 250. 

Having this race will help buy the food to feed these children. It is one of our favorite fundraisers for this cause.

Thank you.

Kylee

We are excited to once again have a Kids Fun Run as part of Homecoming's Scot Trot! This once-around-the-quad run (about a 1/4 mile) is free for all children age 10 and under. Medals will be given to all participants. The Fun Run begins at 8:30 a.m. will take only a few minutes to complete, even at a walking pace!  

The 5K trail race will start promptly at 9 a.m. Check in opens at 7:30 a.m. on the main quad at the center of campus, with day-of registration closing at 8:30 a.m. Parking is in the lot behind the Jenks Library at the rear of campus.

The race will be timed by North Shore Timing Company.

Event details and schedule

7:30 -8:45am Registration / Packet Pick-Up

8:30am Kids 1K Fun Run

9am Scot Trot 5K Trail Race

Course Details

The course is almost completely flat with a few small hills. The race will begin at the center of campus with a full loop around the quad. Participants will run through the Gordon woods for great views of the foliage and return to the quad for a final lap. The course will be well marked with mileage signs.

Awards
Award ceremony immediately following all runner's completion of the race. Prizes for 1st, 2nd and 3rd place and apple pies for male and female and age division winners.

NEW THIS YEAR FOR THE 10 YEAR ANNIVERSARY OF THE SCOT TROT

// Cool Max shirts for all the participants registering before September 12.

// Ten items will be placed throughout the course and any runner who takes a picture of all ten will be entered into a drawing for a great prize!

Join us for the 5th Annual Run for the Hills. Enjoy beautiful scenery and fall colors along rolling country roads past farms and fields in the beautiful Berkshire Hills. Event includes 5K, 10K distances and a kid's 1K fun run.

All proceeds benefit Great Barrington Land Conservancy - Promoting land conservation, farm preservation, and community trails since 1992. 

Race day check-in and final registration runs from 8-9 am. Registration closes at 9 am sharp. 

The 10K start time is 9:20 am. The 10K starting area is located near the Kilpatrick Athletic Center on the Simon's Rock entrance road. 

The 5K start time is 9:40 am. The 5K starting area is located on Alford Road just north of the Simon's Rock entrance in front of Seekonk Veterinary Clinic. 

A FREE kids 1K fun run will take place immediately following the 5K and 10K (at approximately 10:30 am). The 1K starting area is located near the entrance to the Kilpatrick Athletic Center. The kids fun run is on a paved trail around the lower pond near the Simon's Rock entrance.

Light refreshments and brief awards ceremony will be held at the Kilpatrick Athletic Center at Simon's Rock immediately after the events.
